    "description": [
        {
            "text": "\"Linear Electric Linear Current Density\" is the electric current per unit length. Electric current, $I$, through a curve $C$ is defined as $I = \\int_C J _s \\times e_n$, where $e_n$ is a unit vector perpendicular to the surface and line vector element, and $dr$ is the differential of position vector $r$.",
            "lang": "en"
        }
